<subSubSection id="C337088DF762B123B182FE4830D4418F" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F762B123B182FE48374D41E8" blockId="23.[151,1437,331,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F762B123B182FE4832C2428C" box="[199,251,439,465]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F762B123B032FE4830444293" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[375,637,438,465]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 103)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned both males and females in his original description. From his acquisition catalogue he apparently had 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF762B123B3E0FE24316F42B7" box="[677,854,475,501]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
at hand when he described the species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F762B123B479FE24335D415B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="23" pageNumber="544" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 51)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 569705 [4701] as a “type”, which we treat as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F762B123B53BFE0036D3415B" box="[1150,1258,511,537]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected at Durban on 
<date id="FF937DC6F762B123B32CFDDC310C417F" box="[617,821,547,573]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" value="1839-10-26">26 October 1839</date>
. The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF762B123B23DFDDC3665417F" box="[888,1116,547,573]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">four paralectotypes</specimenCount>
are: NRM 537663 [4700], a mounted female collected at Durban on 
<date id="FF937DC6F762B123B3CAFDB9315F4123" box="[655,870,582,609]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" value="1839-12-05">5 December 1839</date>
; NRM 90166584 [6721], a female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F762B123B43AFDB9331741C7" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" value="1840-08-15">15 August 1840</date>
at Durban; NRM 90166583 [4699], a female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F762B123B2F3FD94360641C7" box="[950,1087,619,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" value="1839-07-08">8 July 1839</date>
at Durban; and a male [6720] from Durban, collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F762B123B0F5FD70306941EB" box="[432,592,655,681]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" value="1840-06-18">18 June 1840</date>
, exchanged to 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F762B123B3BAFD70317141EB" box="[767,840,655,681]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 1853 (but no longer in the ZMB collection).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F762B123B182FD4C30D4418F" blockId="23.[151,1437,331,933]" box="[199,749,691,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">
<materialsCitation id="3B45515BF762B123B182FD4C30D1418F" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766756336" box="[199,744,691,717]" collectionCode="VERIFIED" location="Durban" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="KwaZulu-Natal" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F762B123B182FD4C331A4188" box="[199,291,691,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">VERIFIED</collectionCode>
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F762B123B06FFD4533624188" box="[298,347,698,714]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">TYPE</typeStatus>
LOCALITY: 
<location id="8EF20DDDF762B123B096FD4C3013418F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F762B123B1D2FEFC373740E7:8EF20DDDF762B123B096FD4C3013418F" box="[467,554,691,717]" name="Durban" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" stateProvince="KwaZulu-Natal">Durban</location>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F762B123B370FD4C30D1418F" box="[565,744,691,717]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF762B123B182FD28373740E7" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F762B123B182FD28373740E7" blockId="23.[151,1437,331,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">
COMMENTS: The TL was incorrectly restricted to Umkomaas River by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F762B123B293FD2836F841B3" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[982,1217,727,753]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" pagination="264 - 292" refId="ref28785" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1934) The travels and collections of Johan August Wahlberg, 1810 - 1856: a pioneer naturalist in South Africa. Ibis, 76, 264 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1934. tb 01567. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Gyldenstolpe (1934)</bibRefCitation>
. Wahlberg returned to Durban from Umkomaas on 11 September and remained there until 29 October when he travelled north-east to the Tugela (Thukela) River. NRM 90166644 [6722], a male collected 13 January (or perhaps June?) 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F762B123B441FCE03763407B" box="[1284,1370,799,825]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68376" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" unit="in" value="1844.0">1844 in</quantity>
Saulspoort, was recorded by Sundevall in the manuscript catalogue after two 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F762B123B285FCBC3682401F" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[960,1211,835,861]" class="Aves" family="Cisticolidae" genus="Camaroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="olivacea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F762B123B285FCBC3682401F" box="[960,1211,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">Camaroptera olivacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “a dist. sp.”. Following Article 72.4.1 of the Code: “or doubtfully attributes to the taxon”, this specimen, presently identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F762B123B1D2FC74313740E7" authority="von Zedlitz, 1911" authorityName="von Zedlitz" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,782,907,933]" class="Aves" family="Cisticolidae" genus="Camaroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="544" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicaudata" subSpecies="sharpei">
<emphasis id="B9598714F762B123B1D2FC74300C40E7" box="[151,565,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">Camaroptera brevicaudata sharpei</emphasis>
von Zedlitz, 1911
</taxonomicName>
, is not included in the original 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F762B123B53EFC74369740E7" box="[1147,1198,907,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="544">type</typeStatus>
series..
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
